\i \cf2 Pricing\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720

\i0 \cf0 This is tricky, and something that needs to be discussed at length and which I need to be involved in. Highly slashing prices, or introducing monthly fees, I believe are ways that devalue and trivialise the experience. I think, aside from testing, there should be a payment for access, in which is included \'93ownable\'94 items; a transcript of the experience, extra content, music. DRM also is not needed as the music is tied to experience; no-one will substitute for the entire experience, which is convoluted and not an easily \'93ownable\'94 environment. You cannot steal an environment.  I\'92m also not sure about tiers of pricing; does this say that for more money you can understand it \'93more\'94? Extra content for more money, sure, but for unlocking content? I think that there should be a flat fee. It is still a question whether sales and low prices actually do devalue experiences, but it is a valid one. And where can value be added if it is necessary? I should look for ways to give people rewards without people paying for them. \
