\f3 \cf0 DRM clearly does not work. It may keep people out for a little while, but you fight a losing battle that damages legitimate customers. This has been shown time and time again, and books, and digital works, are just entering this field. Would it not be wonderful if we could actually 
\i learn 
\i0 from these mistakes in other mediums and bypass them, saving lots of money and surprising everybody? It should not be a novelty for a company to trust its customers, but it is.  \
