\i \cf3 Failbetter\'92s Methods\cf0 \
\

\i0 On the whole, I am a fan of Failbetter\'92s approach. Fallen London is fun, literate and different. I\'92m 
\f0 not a big fan of the "Echo This" options everywhere, and feel that there should be an automatic journalling of what happens, in an attractive format, to streamline the UI. The menus aren't nested well, or spell-checked. Despite all the \'93ethical\'94 treatment, there 
\i is 
\i0 still manipulation. Convenience always wins, so how far should the clasping of the hand go? Part of the issue is that it is still, after all, grinding. But the story is read maybe once, and then a second time, and this repetition does have its place. I need to find the middle way, or the fairest way
\fs28 . 
\fs24 There is a push towards monetization in Failbetter\'92s methods, and I am starting to understand the reason for this. Freemium works because people do not bounce off a paywall - an honest policy is what is needed, not a complete dismissal of the freemium model. Most people pay for fate to grind, and so the freemium model does need to be tweaked, as the grind is not something we want to emulate. 
